\emph default
 depend on the Power in question: claws and laser-beam eyes have the exact
 same Combat Range for a given Scope, they simply require different descriptions
 of how the power is used to justify them, with claws more likely to require
 extra justification by including a description of how the character runs
 and leaps on the foe, or slashes a cable holding a cargo net to make it
 fall on him.
 In any case, by the Primary Rule if you can't come up with a plausible
 justification given the circumstances, you should refrain from using the
 power until it is justified.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each Round you can try to reduce or increase the Range by one category;
 if the other side tries to prevent that from happening (by fleeing or pursuing)
