\begin_layout Standard
Wealth is an optional system in Zap! Many Science Fiction settings make
 the character's wealth irrelevant, or just part of the background: the
 characters are doing what they do to make money, but how much money is
 never really described nor do their actions seem particularly constrained
 by what things cost.
 Even if the setting doesn't suppose a post-scarcity economy, if you're
 on active duty and bankrolled by Star Fleet, how much it took to build
 your ship or to keep it running and in repair need never come up.
 On the other hand, a space-navy campaign might well have the captain of
 a ship assigned a budget that she needs to keep within, or have her personal
 wealth matter in terms her share of prizes awarded for the capture of enemy
 vessels.
\end_layout

